<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T17:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T17:30:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/710: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Singapore</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Patton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Singapore</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-08T06:00:00+07:30">December
                                    8, 1941—6 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 8—5:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>339. Japanese raided Singapore 4 a.m. today and airfield Tengah nearby.
                            They also landed troops at Kota Bharu, northern Kelantan and heavy
                            fighting reported here. Damages light here, no casualties reported among
                            Americans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Patton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>